cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use AgentOS in research or a product, please cite it as below."
title: "AgentOS: a repo-local operating system for AI coding agents"
abstract: >-
  AgentOS is a runtime-agnostic governance kernel for AI coding agents. It installs a
  canonical agent-os/ directory of rules, review gates, workflows, and durable memory
  into any project, plus thin adapters that activate those rules inside Claude Code,
  OpenAI Codex, and other AGENTS.md-aware runtimes. Its signature mechanism is a
  hook-enforced per-turn audit trail: a turn cannot finish until the agent has logged a
  well-formed, uniquely-numbered audit entry.
